## 7.4 Full Design Checklist

- Are the main modules and module boundaries covered?
- Are the main call chains and key exception paths covered?
- Are the core data / state / resource models covered?
- Are API contracts, error models, and permission boundaries covered?
- Are performance, security, and testability goals covered?
- Are recommended options clearly separated from confirmed decisions?

Record important decisions in `docs/adr/` when appropriate. Long-lived structural and behavioral truths should be captured in `docs/knowledge/structure/README.md` and `docs/knowledge/behavior/README.md`.

